                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Suzlon rights okayed
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                               
	Mumbai, Sept. 29: Wind turbine maker Suzlon Energy Ltd today received the approval of its board to raise up to Rs 1,800 crore through a rights issue of equity shares.         
	The terms and conditions of the rights issue, including the rights entitlement ratio, the issue price and the record date, will be announced by the board of directors in four to five weeks after receiving the due approvals.         
	The proceeds from the proposed rights issue will be used to buy Portuguese conglomerate Martifiers stake in REpower Systems AG and for the potential buyout of any minority shares that are offered.        
	The companys board of directors has also approved a plan by IDFC Private Equity to invest Rs 400 crore for a 17.1 per cent stake in SE Forge, a wholly owned subsidiary of Suzlon.         
	The transaction values SE Forge at around Rs 2, 300 crore.                                                                                                                                                          
